# Shader & Build Integration

Applies to the rewrite (`next/nlrc_vksplat/`). Differs from ref, which loads `.spv` from disk at runtime.

## Build-time compilation

1. CMake compiles shaders to SPIR-V at build time
2. SPIR-V converts to C++ headers as `uint32_t` bytecode arrays
3. C++ includes the generated header and passes the array to `VkShaderModuleCreateInfo`

```cpp
// BAD — runtime disk load (ref pattern, not for rewrite)
createComputePipeline(pipeline, "shader/generated/foo.spv");

// GOOD — embedded bytecode
#include "generated/foo_spirv.hpp"
createShaderModule(std::vector<uint32_t>(foo_spirv, foo_spirv + foo_spirv_len), &module);
```

## Shader languages

- Slang: all core compute kernels
- GLSL 460: radix sort only (`shader/radix_sort/*.comp`)

## Config propagation

`vksplat_config.h` drives `VKSPLAT_*` constants. Port or reuse logic from `ref/vksplat/scripts/generate_shader_config.py` to emit Slang/GLSL fragments and `shader_config.json`.

## CMake dependencies

Editing `.slang`, `.comp`, or `.glsl` must rebuild the generated header and any C++ TU that includes it.

## Porting reference

Shader sources to port from: `ref/vksplat/slang/` and `ref/vksplat/shader/radix_sort/`.
